channel.title: Compile help/error with CheezScape
channel.description:
Ok, so, I have CheezScape v80, and whenever I compile it, and runserver(I've tried the file complie, then runserver, the file run&compile), but any changes that I made NEVER happen ingame, it just stays the same as when i first extracted it from the zip. I'm thinking that maybe an error when it compiles causes it to do this, but I don't know. Any help?
The error is: [code] client.java:5147: unreachable statement if(item == 4708 && playerLevel[13] >= 85) ^ Note: stream.java uses or overrides a deprecated API. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:depracation for details. 1 error Press any key to continue . . . [/code]
If that has nothing to do with no changes ingame, can you tell me what I am doing wrong, and why my changes in client.java don't take effect after I compile and run the server? I don't know why it's like this, This [i]is[/i] my first time with CheezScape though, and it is from Whitescape, I believe. I always used Project16, so I'm probobly doing something wrong when compiling.[br][size=1]Posted at: November 12, 2006, 03:20:31 PM[/size][hr]I'm desperate here, Can someone help me?[br][size=1]Posted at: November 12, 2006, 08:32:03 PM[/size][hr]Does anyone out there know why my changes aren't going ingame after compiling?[br][size=1]Posted at: November 12, 2006, 10:43:10 PM[/size][hr]Sorry for being impatient, but the RS2 Server Development/Help page can't be found, So I'm trying to have people read this as the latest topic. So does anyone know how to help me?[br][size=1]Posted at: November 13, 2006, 12:15:43 AM[/size][hr]It's been a whole day...
Maybe someone will help me now since the forums were being retarded yesterday :D
